FREE ASSOCIATION PROTOCOL v6: SATISFACTION-BASED LEARNING
(Asynchronous, Event-Driven, Non-Blocking)
(Manual Acceptance by Default, Optional Policy-Based Automation)

💡 KEY PRINCIPLES:
   1. MS Formula Throughout: MS(provider, recipient) = MR × recipient_share
      Bootstrap: share = recognition (no satisfaction data yet)
      Learned: share = (recognition × satisfaction) / Σ
      Same formula, evolving shares = principled learning
   
   2. Allocation → Offer Separation: Allocation (derived) → Offer (commitment)
      Providers compute allocations via MS formula (automatic)
      Apply offering_policy to create offers (commitment_rate × allocation)
      Creates provider optionality and convexity
   
   3. Flexible Acceptance: Manual (default) or Policy-Based (optional)
      Strategies: manual, 1/N (antifragile), weighted, greedy
      Set once in tree, executes automatically if enabled

