ually (bounded downside, unbounded upside)<br/>   - weighted: Proportional to reputation<br/>   - greedy: Accept from best first<br/>   - manual: Default per-cycle review<br/>   💡 Trade-off: automation vs control<br/><br/>8. SATISFACTION RATING (Async):<br/>   - Recipients rate over time (hours/days)<br/>   - No blocking on satisfaction<br/>   - Measures actual utility, not belief<br/>   - Creates accountability loop<br/><br/>9. AUTOMATIC LEARNING (Reactive):<br/>   - Satisfaction adjusts recipient shares<br/>   - MS formula uses updated shares<br/>   - High satisfaction → larger share → more allocation<br/>   - Low satisfaction → smaller share → less allocation<br/>   - Seamless learning without formula changes<br/><br/>10. PROVIDER QUALITY SIGNALS:<br/>   - Providers observe their satisfaction ratings<br/>   - Learn which recipients they serve well<br/>   - Can adjust offerings based on feedback<br/><br/>11. CONVERGENCE TO UTILITY:<br/>   - System learns what actually works<br/>   - Not just what people believe works<br/>   - Empirically grounded allocation
